{
    "attributes": {
        "action": "Revise the Current 'Right to Repair' regulations",
        "additional_details": "Right to repair regulations make it law that when you buy certain products, you have a right to repair them when they break - but it does not include smartphones, tablets or laptops. This means that people are trapped in a constant cycle of replacing these pieces of tech.\r\n \r\nThis is bad for the environment, bad for your pocket, and only good for the profit of huge companies.",
        "background": "We demand that the UK Government revise the current \u2018right to repair\u2019 regulations to include smartphones, cordless phones, tablets, and laptops.",
